{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T08:57:22.124Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Optimizer Step — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Optimizer Step Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "optimizer step"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the final step in each iteration of the training loop where the model's parameters (weights and biases) are actually updated. It uses the gradients computed during the backward pass to adjust parameters in a way that reduces the loss."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The optimizer performs an optimization step: it updates the values of the model's parameters based on the gradients. This is where the model "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "actually learns"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — the mathematical adjustments happen here to improve future predictions."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Optimizer Step Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Different optimizers use different approaches to decide how much to update and in which direction:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use Case in Generative AI"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Basic gradient descent: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "W = W - lr grad"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Simple GANs, older models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD + Momentum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Accumulates past gradients: smoother updates"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Diffusion models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adaptive learning rates per parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Most GANs, transformers, LLMs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AdamW"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adam with decoupled weight decay"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "State-of-the-art: StyleGAN, diffusion"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RMSprop"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scales gradients by running average"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Video generation, temporal models"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The direction of updates depends on the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "gradient's sign"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Positive gradient"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Parameter should decrease to reduce loss → update is negative\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Negative gradient"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Parameter should increase to reduce loss → update is positive"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Optimizer Step Works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In the Training Loop Context"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Complete training loop with optimizer step\nfor epoch in range(epochs):\n    for batch in dataset:\n        # 1. Get batch\n        inputs, labels = batch\n        \n        # 2. Zero gradient (clear old gradients)\n        optimizer.zero_grad()  # [web:106][web:107][web:108]\n        \n        # 3. Forward pass\n        outputs = model(inputs)  # [web:106][web:107]\n        \n        # 4. Loss computation\n        loss = criterion(outputs, labels)  # [web:106][web:107]\n        \n        # 5. Backward pass\n        loss.backward()  # [web:106][web:107][web:108]\n        \n        # 6. OPTIMIZER STEP ← what we're explaining\n        optimizer.step()  # [web:106][web:107][web:108]\n        \n        # 7. Logging\n        print(f\"Loss: {loss.item()}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "optimizer.step()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Does"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# PyTorch optimizer step\noptimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\n\n# After backward pass: gradients stored in param.grad\nloss.backward()\n\n# Optimizer step: update parameters\noptimizer.step()  # [web:108][web:109]\n\n# What happens internally:\n# For each parameter P with gradient G:\n# P_new = P_old - lr * G  # (for SGD)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "step()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " method will use the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".grad"}, {"type": "text", "text": " attributes of all trainable parameters passed to the optimizer to update them using the update formula (e.g., it could include momentum etc.)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Update Formula"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W_{\\text{new}} = W_{\\text{old}} - \\text{lr} \\times \\frac{\\partial \\text{Loss}}{\\partial W}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Weight parameter\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{lr}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Learning rate (e.g., 0.001)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial \\text{Loss}}{\\partial W}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient of loss w.r.t. weight"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam optimizer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (more complex):"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "m_t = \\beta_1 m_{t-1} + (1-\\beta_1) \\times g_t  \\quad \\text{(momentum)}"}}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "v_t = \\beta_2 v_{t-1} + (1-\\beta_2) \\times g_t^{2}  \\quad \\text{(adaptive scaling)}"}}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W_{\\text{new}} = W_{\\text{old}} - \\text{lr} \\times \\frac{m_t}{\\sqrt{v_t} + \\epsilon}"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer Step in PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Instantiating the Optimizer"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.optim as optim\n\n# Model\nmodel = nn.Linear(128, 784)\n\n# Loss function (criterion)\ncriterion = nn.MSELoss()  # [web:106]\n\n# Optimizer (define once outside loop)\noptimizer = optim.SGD(\n    model.parameters(),   # Which parameters to optimize [web:106]\n    lr=0.01               # Learning rate [web:106]\n)\n\n# COMMON: Adam optimizer\noptimizer = optim.Adam(\n    model.parameters(),\n    lr=0.001              # Typical lr for GANs/transformers\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complete Training Loop"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Training loop\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    for inputs, labels in dataset:\n        # 1. Clear gradients\n        optimizer.zero_grad()  # [web:106][web:108]\n        \n        # 2. Forward pass\n        outputs = model(inputs)  # [web:106]\n        \n        # 3. Loss computation\n        loss = criterion(outputs, labels)  # [web:106]\n        \n        # 4. Backward pass\n        loss.backward()  # [web:106]\n        \n        # 5. Optimizer step\n        optimizer.step()  # [web:106][web:108]\n        \n        # 6. Logging\n        print(f\"Epoch {epoch}, Loss: {loss.item()}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Optimizer Methods"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# 1. zero_grad() - Clear old gradients\noptimizer.zero_grad()\n\n# 2. step() - Update parameters\noptimizer.step()\n\n# 3. State inspection (for advanced optimizers like Adam)\nprint(optimizer.state_dict()['param_states'][0]['m'])  # Momentum\nprint(optimizer.state_dict()['param_states'][0]['v'])  # Variance"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer Step in TensorFlow/Keras"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using Optimizer with GradientTape"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import tensorflow as tf\n\n# Model\nmodel = tf.keras.Sequential([\n    tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu', input_shape=(128,)),\n    tf.keras.layers.Dense(784, activation='sigmoid')\n])\n\n# Loss function\nloss_fn = tf.keras.losses.MeanSquaredError()\n\n# Optimizer\noptimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)  # [web:91]\n\n# Training step\ninputs = tf.random.normal([32, 128])\nlabels = tf.random.normal([32, 784])\n\n# Forward pass with gradient tracking\nwith tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n    predictions = model(inputs, training=True)  # [web:91]\n    loss = loss_fn(labels, predictions)  # [web:91]\n\n# Compute gradients (backward pass)\ngradients = tape.gradient(loss, model.trainable_variables)  # [web:91]\n\n# OPTIMIZER STEP\noptimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients, model.trainable_variables))  # [web:91][web:106]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complete Training Loop"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Complete training loop\nEPOCHS = 10\nfor epoch in range(EPOCHS):\n    total_loss = 0\n    for images, labels in train_ds:\n        with tf.GradientTape() as tape:\n            # Forward pass\n            predictions = model(images, training=True)  # [web:91]\n            \n            # Loss computation\n            loss = loss_fn(labels, predictions)  # [web:91]\n        \n        # Compute gradients\n        gradients = tape.gradient(loss, model.trainable_variables)  # [web:91]\n        \n        # OPTIMIZER STEP\n        optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients, model.trainable_variables))  # [web:91][web:106]\n        \n        total_loss += loss.numpy()\n    \n    print(f\"Epoch {epoch}, Loss: {total_loss / len(train_ds)}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Connection Between Backward Pass and Optimizer Step"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How They Work Together"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# BACKWARD PASS stores gradients\nloss.backward()  # Autograd computes gradients [web:109]\n# After this:\n# - model.weight.grad = ∂loss/∂weight\n# - model.bias.grad = ∂loss/∂bias\n\n# OPTIMIZER STEP uses gradients\noptimizer.step()  # Independent of backward pass [web:109]\n# Optimizer uses the `grad` attribute computed by backward pass [web:109]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Points"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Backward Pass"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer Step"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Input"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss tensor"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradients (in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".grad"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradients stored in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".grad"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Updated parameters"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dependency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Needs forward pass outputs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Needs backward pass gradients"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Link"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implicit (via "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".grad"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uses results from backward"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "They are linked "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "implicitly"}, {"type": "text", "text": " only by the fact that the optimizer will use the results computed by the backward preceding call."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning Rate and Its Impact"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Small learning rate (0.0001)\n# - Slow but stable learning\n# - Good for fine-tuning models\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.0001)\n\n# Medium learning rate (0.001)\n# - Standard for most models\n# - Good balance of speed/stability\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\n\n# Large learning rate (0.01)\n# - Fast but unstable\n# - May overshoot optimal weights\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.01)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The size of the update depends on:\n1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Controls step size\n2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient magnitude"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Larger gradients = larger updates\n3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimizer state"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Momentum, adaptive scaling (Adam)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Issues with Optimizer Step"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Not Zeroing Gradients"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# WRONG: Gradients accumulate\nfor batch in dataset:\n    outputs = model(inputs)\n    loss = criterion(outputs, labels)\n    loss.backward()\n    optimizer.step()  # Gradients from batch 1 + batch 2 + ...\n\n# RIGHT: Zero gradients first\nfor batch in dataset:\n    optimizer.zero_grad()  # Clear old gradients [web:106][web:108]\n    outputs = model(inputs)\n    loss = criterion(outputs, labels)\n    loss.backward()\n    optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Optimizer and Model Parameters"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# WRONG: Optimizer doesn't know about model\noptimizer = optim.Adam()  # No parameters!\nmodel.trainable_params = model.parameters()\noptimizer.step()  # ERROR!\n\n# RIGHT: Pass parameters to optimizer\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters())  # [web:109]\noptimizer.step()  # Updates model.parameters()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Gradient Clipping (Before optimizer.step())"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Common practice: Manipulate gradients before step\nloss.backward()\n\n# Clip gradients to prevent exploding gradients\ntorch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)  # [web:108]\n\noptimizer.step()  # Safe update [web:108]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimizer Step in Generative AI Models"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GAN Training Loop"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Discriminator optimizer\nd_optimizer = optim.Adam(discriminator.parameters(), lr=0.0002)\n\n# Generator optimizer\ng_optimizer = optim.Adam(generator.parameters(), lr=0.0002)\n\n# Training loop\nfor real_images in dataset:\n    # Train discriminator\n    d_optimizer.zero_grad()  # [web:106][web:108]\n    real_pred = discriminator(real_images)\n    fake_images = generator(noise)\n    fake_pred = discriminator(fake_images)\n    d_loss = compute_d_loss(real_pred, fake_pred)\n    d_loss.backward()  # [web:106]\n    d_optimizer.step()  # Update discriminator [web:106][web:108]\n    \n    # Train generator\n    g_optimizer.zero_grad()  # [web:106][web:108]\n    fake_images = generator(noise)\n    fake_pred = discriminator(fake_images)\n    g_loss = compute_g_loss(fake_pred)\n    g_loss.backward()  # [web:106]\n    g_optimizer.step()  # Update generator [web:106][web:108]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Diffusion Model Training Loop"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "optimizer = optim.AdamW(diffusion_model.parameters(), lr=0.0001)\n\nfor images in dataset:\n    optimizer.zero_grad()  # [web:106][web:108]\n    \n    # Forward pass\n    t = random_timesteps(batch_size)\n    noise = torch.randn_like(images)\n    noisy_images = add_noise(images, noise, t)\n    predicted_noise = diffusion_model(noisy_images, t)\n    \n    # Loss\n    loss = criterion(predicted_noise, noise)\n    \n    # Backward pass\n    loss.backward()  # [web:106]\n    \n    # Gradient clipping (common in diffusion)\n    torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(diffusion_model.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)\n    \n    # Optimizer step\n    optimizer.step()  # Update diffusion model [web:106][web:108]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of the optimizer step as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "a hiker adjusting their path"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forward pass"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Hiker takes a step (makes prediction)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Hiker measures distance from target (error)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backward pass"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Hiker calculates slope direction (gradients)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimizer step"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Hiker moves downhill (updates weights)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": How big each step is"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The optimizer is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "mechanism that actually changes the model's weights"}, {"type": "text", "text": " based on the learned gradients."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimizer step"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Final step where model parameters are updated"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Purpose"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Reduce loss by adjusting weights/biases in right direction"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "optimizer.step()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Updates parameters using gradients from backward pass"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "W_new = W_old - lr * gradient"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adaptive learning rate with momentum"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Controls update size (typical: 0.001 for GANs/transformers)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "optimizer.zero_grad()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Must clear old gradients before backward"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "PyTorch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "optimizer.step()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".grad"}, {"type": "text", "text": " attributes computed by backward"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "TensorFlow"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "optimizer.apply_gradients(zip(gradients, variables))"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimizer instantiation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Must pass "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "model.parameters()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to optimizer"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backward pass dependency"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Optimizer uses results computed by backward"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient clipping"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Manipulate gradients before "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "step()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (common practice)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No learning in testing"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Testing loop omits backward + optimizer step"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generative AI"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adam/AdamW standard for GANs, diffusion, transformers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model actually learns"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": This is where mathematical adjustments happen"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The optimizer's task is to take the parameters of the model independently and update them using a given optimization routine (SGD, Adam, RMSprop, etc.). While the backward pass computes gradients, the optimizer step "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "applies"}, {"type": "text", "text": " those gradients to actually improve the model's predictions."}]}]}}